# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — keep the repo lean while still reproducing the best model.
#
# What stays tracked (the reproduction path):
#   src/  reproduce/  analysis/*.py  analysis/figures/*.png
#   README.md  REPORT.md  requirements.txt  sample_submission.csv
#   the SMALL prediction caches in cache/*.npz that reproduce/build_finals.py needs
#
# What is ignored: raw data, logs, generated submissions, archived experiments,
# and the bulky/regenerable cache artifacts (raw-array, feature, checkpoint files).
# =============================================================================

# ---- raw dataset (restore from Kaggle to retrain from scratch) --------------
Dataset/
train/
test/
*.zip

# ---- logs & scratch output --------------------------------------------------
*.log
logs/
_*.txt
*_out.txt
*_err.txt

# ---- generated submissions (regenerate: python reproduce/build_finals.py) ---
submission/*.csv

# ---- archived / experimental material (not needed to reproduce the finals) --
archive/
catboost_info/

# ---- python -----------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
*.ipynb

# ---- agent / editor state ---------------------------------------------------
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# ---- bulky / regenerable cache artifacts ------------------------------------
# Keep the small prediction caches (cache/*.npz model outputs) so the finals
# reproduce; exclude raw-array, feature, checkpoint, and intermediate files.
# (These are rebuilt from the dataset via the src/ pipeline.)
cache/windows.npz
cache/features*.npz
cache/*.pt
cache/*.npy
cache/tcn_embed_*.npz
cache/*_history.json
cache/*.sh

# orphaned experiment-scratch outputs (their scripts live in archive/experiments/)
cache/_exp_*.npz
cache/exp1_binary.npz
cache/exp3_rescue.npz
cache/_catboost_p*.npz

REPORT.md